Privacy Policy for Notely

Notely respects your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how your information is handled when you use our application.

1. Information We Collect

Notely does not collect, store, or share any personal data.
All reminders you create are stored locally on your device only.

No account creation is required and no personal information is requested.

2. Notifications

Notely uses local notifications to remind you of your scheduled tasks.
These notifications are created and managed entirely on your device.

No notification data is sent to any server.

3. Data Sharing

Notely does not share your data with third parties.
We do not use analytics services, advertising networks, or tracking tools.

4. Internet Usage

Notely works completely offline.
No internet connection is required for core features.

5. Data Security

All your data remains on your device and is protected by your system security.
We do not have access to your reminders or any personal information.

6. Childrenâ€™s Privacy

Notely does not knowingly collect data from children under the age of 13.

7. Changes to This Policy

This privacy policy may be updated from time to time.
Any changes will be reflected within the app or on the app store page.

8. Contact

If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, you can contact us at:

Email: support@notely.app

By using Notely, you agree to this Privacy Policy.
